place.name: CRINOW
place.gazetteerText: CRINOW, or Croynwydd, a parish in Narberth district, Pembroke; 1½mile E of Narberth, and 2 SSE of Narberth Road r. station. Post town, Narberth. Acres, 352. Real property, £620. Pop., 70. Houses, 15. The manor belongs to the Eatons. The living is a rectory in the diocese of St. Davids. Value, £86. Patron, the Lord Chancellor. The church is very good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
